<subSubSection id="3B61CDBF8B666330D233DB87F27956D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="393" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A6679C724815C57DF3ED57799F494C1C" pageId="0" pageNumber="393">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="72DCAE02C46C4DDDFEA2B32F0605D5C1" pageId="0" pageNumber="393">
<taxonomicName id="B0659DD07DBB4EB34F8E3E969408EC79" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Aphyocharax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphyocharax pusillus" order="Characiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">Aphyocharax pusillus</taxonomicName>
differs from all of its congeners, except 
<taxonomicName id="EA48F0B00BFDEA3FF2905888E457BEDA" genus="A." lsidName="A. avary" pageId="0" pageNumber="393" rank="species" species="avary">A. avary</taxonomicName>
, by having black or dark brown middle caudal-fin rays (Figs 1-3; 
<bibRefCitation id="921BCB29B379C02B2D7D740ACC8BCFCC" author="Guenther, A" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="393" pagination="423 - 429" title="Descriptions of some species of fishes from the Peruvian Amazons." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1469-7998.1869.tb07347.x" volume="2" year="1869">
<normalizedToken id="D13AEAD756E639B097FB3EC7374E55D5" originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
1869
</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 2). 
<taxonomicName id="BDFBFF8EC2FD328DF236FBFA6B18DC0E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Characidae" genus="Aphyocharax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aphyocharax pusillus" order="Characiformes" pageId="0" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pusillus">Aphyocharax pusillus</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="324BB99164646E9227198272C1359A9E" genus="A." lsidName="A. avary" pageId="0" pageNumber="393" rank="species" species="avary">A. avary</taxonomicName>
by having fewer maxillary teeth, spread along the proximal half of the bone (Fig. 4
<normalizedToken id="B94EF91CB0BF3E16C5BD37D735054278" originalValue="B–G">B-G</normalizedToken>
) [vs. more maxillary teeth spread along 2/3 of the maxillary extension (Fig. 4A].
</paragraph>
